        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): dedupe accounts sharing the local Messages source",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #65141. When `channels.imessage.accounts` contained both `default` and a named account pointing at the same local Messages source, the gateway started two `imsg rpc` watchers and inbound messages were processed twice (one `ping` yielded two `pong` replies).\n\nThis mirrors the Discord duplicate-token pattern (`extensions/discord/src/accounts.ts:172`) for iMessage:\n\n- `resolveIMessageAccountSourceSignature(account)` derives a `(cliPath, dbPath)` signature for the local backend an account targets.\n- `resolveIMessageAccountSourceOwner({ cfg, signature })` picks the canonical owner, **preferring an explicit named account over the implicit `default`** so bindings tied to a named account keep delivering.\n- `isIMessageAccountEnabledForRuntime` / `resolveIMessageAccountDisabledReason` are wired into the iMessage channel config adapter, so the existing Gateway `startAccount` loop (`src/gateway/server-channels.ts:458-473`) skips non-owner duplicates and reports `duplicate iMessage source; using account \"<owner>\"` in runtime state.\n- `imessageDoctor.collectPreviewWarnings` flags the redundant account from `openclaw doctor` with source coordinates and the `enabled: false` silencing tip. The doctor adapter moved from an inline `{ groupAllowFromFallbackToAllowFrom: false }` into a proper `extensions/imessage/src/doctor.ts` to host the new warning.\n\nUser config in the issue (`default` + `swang430-gmail-com`) now starts one `imsg rpc` and the named account keeps receiving the binding, matching the workaround the reporter applied manually.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: duplicate `imsg rpc` watchers and duplicate inbound replies when two enabled iMessage accounts share the local backend.\n\nReal environment tested: synthetic via the new vitest cases; not a live iMessage replay.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs extensions/imessage/src/accounts.ts extensions/imessage/src/accounts.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/channel.ts extensions/imessage/src/doctor.ts extensions/imessage/src/doctor.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/shared.ts\npnpm format:check extensions/imessage/src/accounts.ts extensions/imessage/src/doctor.ts extensions/imessage/src/channel.ts extensions/imessage/src/shared.ts extensions/imessage/src/accounts.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/doctor.test.ts\nnode scripts/check-changelog-attributions.mjs\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: `Test Files 47 passed (47) / Tests 452 passed (452)` across the iMessage extension suite (includes the new collision cases in `accounts.test.ts` and `doctor.test.ts`). Typecheck, lint, formatting, and changelog attribution scans all exit clean.\n\nObserved result after fix: `listEnabledIMessageAccounts(cfg)` returns one account per unique `(cliPath, dbPath)`, the non-owner reports `duplicate iMessage source; using account \"<owner>\"`, and `imessageDoctor.collectPreviewWarnings` emits one `- channels.imessage: accounts \"<owner>\" and \"<dup>\" watch the same local Messages source (cliPath=imsg)...` line per collision group; no warning when only one account is enabled or when each account targets a distinct cliPath.\n\nWhat was not tested: a live Mac with two configured iMessage accounts running `imsg rpc` end-to-end. Not local Crabbox-validated; broader changed lanes are deferred to CI.\n\n## Notes\n\n- No SDK contract or config schema change. Existing iMessage configs continue to load without migration.\n- The owner-preference rule keeps explicit account ids working when paired with `default`. Reverse case (two named accounts targeting the same backend) still dedupes deterministically via `listIMessageAccountIds` order.\n- CHANGELOG entry placed under `## Unreleased` § Fixes, thanking @swang430 who reported the original issue with a complete repro.",
        "branch": "worktree-fix-imessage-default-dup-65141",
